elements.title: Alice Kuperjanov
elements.contents: ... that Alice Kuperjanov (pictured) was one of the founders of the Estonian women's movement and assisted military efforts during the Estonian War of Independence?

elements.title: East Louisiana Railroad
elements.contents: ... that the East Louisiana Railroad, which removed Homer Plessy from a train, actually did so to help him start Plessy v. Ferguson, an attempt to overturn segregation in the United States?

elements.title: Rufina Peter
elements.contents: ... that until Rufina Peter and Kessy Sawang's election in August 2022, Papua New Guinea was one of only three countries without a woman in parliament?

elements.title: Dir, dir, Jehova, will ich singen
elements.contents: ... that "Dir, dir, Jehova, will ich singen" is a 1697 Lutheran hymn, translated into English by Catherine Winkworth in 1863 as "Jehovah, let me now adore Thee"?

elements.title: Larry Kelley
elements.contents: ... that Heisman Trophy winner Larry Kelley turned down multiple offers to play professional football to become a school teacher?

elements.title: Battle of Dunsinane
elements.contents: ... that contrary to Shakespeare's play, Macbeth was not killed during the Battle of Dunsinane?

elements.title: the leader of the Quebec Hells Angels
elements.contents: ... that the leader of the Quebec Hells Angels was acquitted of 13 murder charges because the star witness was unwilling to testify at trial and instead complained about how the Crown had cheated him?

elements.title: Tigris
elements.contents: ... that the design of the train for the roller coaster Tigris was revealed in the form of a cake?
